.TH "LIGHTNING-WALLET-TAG" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-wallet-tag \- append a tag to a ledger entry's note
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning wallet-tag
.I wallet
.I entry_id
.I tag
.SH DESCRIPTION
Appends
.I tag
to the
.B note
field of the ledger entry identified by
.I entry_id
in the specified wallet's database.
Returns
.B {"ok":false}
if the database does not exist or the update fails.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"ok":true}
{"ok":false,"reason":...}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-wallet-ledger-search (1),
.BR lightning-wallet-transaction-log (1)
